The method Base64DecodeStream::read() implements InputStream::read() which 
specifies that "The value byte is returned as an int in the range 0 to 255.".
But the current implementation returns a byte value using implicit cast to an 
integer. The values ends up between -127 and +127.
Current code :
    public int read() throws IOException {
        [...some code...]
        return out_buffer[out_offset++];
    }
The correct behaviour can be simply achieved by adding 256 when the byte is 
negative :
    public int read() throws IOException {
        [...some code...]
        int value = out_buffer[out_offset++];
        if ( value < 0 )
            value += 256;
        return value;
    }
